Calling `map` on an array modifies the elements of that array in place,
overwriting the previous values with the results of the supplied callback function.

frontmatter.shortDescription: Map modifies the elements of the array on which it operates in place
frontmatter.shortCorrection: Map returns a new array populated with the results of the callback function
